<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15975] Improper Popen.wait() return code handling in dev/run-tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15975</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In dev/run-tests.py there&apos;s a line where we effectively do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;retcode = some_popen_instance.wait()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; retcode &amp;gt; 0:
  err
# &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; nothing
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but this code is subtlety wrong because Popen&apos;s return code will be negative if the child process was terminated by a signal: &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.python.org/2/library/subprocess.html#subprocess.Popen.returncode&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.python.org/2/library/subprocess.html#subprocess.Popen.returncode&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should change this to &lt;tt&gt;retcode != 0&lt;/tt&gt; so that we properly error out and exit due to termination by signal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
